## 4. Equivalence groups (collapsed)

### BACL-spectrum family
Members: `BACL_grain_max_ulp`, `max_ulp`, `min_ulp`, `ulp_ratio`, `ulp_spread_log2`.
Representative: **`ulp_spread_log2`**.
Rationale: All derived from the operand-chain ulp vector via BACL pair invariant. `ulp_spread_log2` carries the binade-spread information that single-value BACL_grain misses.

### E family
Members: `E_log2_base_operand`, `base_operand`, `in_sterbenz_cluster`.
Representative: **`E_log2_base_operand`**.
Rationale: All derived from 1-x_term `base_operand` via deterministic transformations (log2, identity, interval test). E retains the most information (continuous).

### Precondition group (demoted)
Members: `conjecture_c_in_normal_range`, `c2_lattice_chain_applies`.
Reclassified as preconditions.
Rationale: Both constant True across all in-scope probes. They function as scope-validity gates, not discriminating observables. Their discriminating value may surface under subnormal probing (out of current scope) or alternative algebraic chains.

